Package edu.ncsu.csc216.stp.model.tests

Class TestCase

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.stp.model.tests.TestCase
  • public class TestCase
extends java.lang.Object
    The TestCase class contains the information about each individual test case including the testCaseId, testType, testDescription, expectedResults, and ILog of TestResults. The TestCase additionally contains a TestPlan that the TestCase belongs to.
    Author:
    Veerendra Gottiveeti, Yi Zhang

      • TestCase

        public TestCase​(java.lang.String testCaseId,
                java.lang.String testType,
                java.lang.String testDescription,
                java.lang.String expectedResults)
        Constructs the TestCase with the given parameters. The testResults field is constructed to an empty Log of TestResults. The testPlan is set to null.
        Parameters:
        testCaseId - Id of the test case
        testType - Type of the test case
        testDescription - Description of the test case
        expectedResults - Expected results of the test case
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if testCaseId is null or empty string
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if testType is null or empty string
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if testDescription is null or empty string
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if expectedResults is null or empty string

        public void addTestResult​(boolean passing,
                          java.lang.String testResult)
        Creates a TestResult from the given values and adds the TestResult to the end of the testResults log. This method throws an IAE if the TestResult cannot be constructed.
        Parameters:
        passing - State of a test if it passes
        testResult - Test results of a test
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the TestResult cannot be constructed

      • isTestCasePassing

        public boolean isTestCasePassing()
        Returns true if the last TestResult in the Log is passing. If there are no TestResults in the Log the test is considered failing since it has not yet run and false is returned.
        Returns:
        false if the test is failing or there are no TestResults in the Log, otherwise return true

      • getStatus

      • getActualResultsLog

        public java.lang.String getActualResultsLog()
        Returns a string representation of the testResults Log. A leading “- “ is added to the start of each TestResult and a “\n” is added to the end.
        Returns:
        a string representation of the testResults Log
